The paper proposes a new visual cognition model that focuses on object recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The model is inspired by biological mechanisms, which suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning and feature extraction, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). The concept formation and feature re-selection aspects of the model suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the interaction between neuroscience and information science, which suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
